genresAdvancedInfo.name: vaikiskos dainos
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Vaikiskos dainos, or Lithuanian children's songs, are a beloved part of the country's musical tradition. These catchy tunes are sung by children and adults alike, and often feature simple, memorable melodies and playful lyrics. Many vaikiskos dainos have been passed down through generations, and are an important part of Lithuanian cultural identity.
